<br He was hospitalized in severe conditions and a few hours later died, according to Bbc citing the subsidiary CBS News. The same ex-president was inside the court but left him while the tragic event was underway. According to security officials, there were no dangers to the court and Trump, who in any case was protected by the escort.
&nbsp;
Azzarello had arrived in New York from his house in Florida last week. He had no criminal record > and his family had no knowledge of his trip. New York police chief, Jeffrey Maddrey, said he had been seen "tracing around" in the park before taking out his bag the flammable liquid and pamphlets.
&nbsp;
When he set fire, there was a massive police presence outside the court and the agents ran quickly in the park screaming to ask for an extinguisher, but when he was taken away in the stretcher the burns were very extensive and his serious conditions. Three New York police officers and a court officer reported minor injuries after helping to shut down the fire.

